SIMPLE: gilding
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gilding
<hw>Gild"ing</hw> <pr>(g⟦icr⟧ld"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The art or practice of overlaying or covering with gold leaf; also,
a thin coating or wash of gold, or of that which resembles
gold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Gold in leaf, powder, or liquid, for application to
any surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Any superficial coating or appearance, as opposed to
what is solid and genuine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gilding metal</b></col>, <cd>a tough kind of sheet brass
from which cartridge shells are made.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gile</ent>⟦br⟧
